{"id": "the_state_of_games_april_2026", "source_key": "thegamebusiness", "source": "thegamebusiness.com", "section": "deep_analysis", "title": "The State of Games: April 2026", "url": "https://www.thegamebusiness.com/p/the-state-of-games-april-2026", "published_at": "2026-05-29T18:33:53", "author": "Christopher Dring", "excerpt": "Big month for Tomodachi Life, Pragmata, video game movies and.... Arrows", "text": "Welcome to the latest State of Games Report from The Game Business.\nEvery month, exclusively for paid subscribers, we dive into the key charts, statistics, facts and stories from the previous month in video games, including some exclusive data and analysis from us.\nInterested in becoming a paid subscriber? You will find the link below.\nThe State of Games: April 2026\nThe new releases slowed slightly in April, but there were still some interesting success stories. Nintendo’s second Tomodachi Life game proved to be a real hit, while there was a big breakout new IP success in Pragmata.\nIn mobile, a couple of Arrows made it into the download charts, while video game movies scored big in the trailer department.\nBut it was a tougher month for game consoles, with few major releases and a big price rise for PS5.\nTomodachi Life delivers big numbers, while Pragmata shifts 2m copies\nIn terms of PC and console games, the MAU chart is eerily familiar, but the US games chart from Circana (which features estimated digital sales for the first time), contains a number of new IP and a No.1 for Nintendo.\nRead more", "html": "<p><em>Welcome to the latest State of Games Report from The Game Business.</em></p><p><em>Every month, exclusively for paid subscribers, we dive into the key charts, statistics, facts and stories from the previous month in video games, including some exclusive data and analysis from us.</em></p><p><em>Interested in becoming a paid subscriber? You will find the link below.</em></p><div><hr></div><h2><strong>The State of Games: April 2026</strong></h2><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!vR8o!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F781636b3-06b5-45fe-a093-b6a7ec7bf03e_2694x1432.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!vR8o!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F781636b3-06b5-45fe-a093-b6a7ec7bf03e_2694x1432.png\" width=\"1456\" height=\"774\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/781636b3-06b5-45fe-a093-b6a7ec7bf03e_2694x1432.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:774,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:4804804,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.thegamebusiness.com/i/199635323?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F781636b3-06b5-45fe-a093-b6a7ec7bf03e_2694x1432.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"\"></picture><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\"><svg role=\"img\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>The new releases slowed slightly in April, but there were still some interesting success stories. Nintendo&#8217;s second Tomodachi Life game proved to be a real hit, while there was a big breakout new IP success in Pragmata. <br><br>In mobile, a couple of Arrows made it into the download charts, while video game movies scored big in the trailer department.<br><br>But it was a tougher month for game consoles, with few major releases and a big price rise for PS5.</p><div><hr></div><h3>Tomodachi Life delivers big numbers, while Pragmata shifts 2m copies</h3><p>In terms of PC and console games, the MAU chart is eerily familiar, but the US games chart from Circana (which features estimated digital sales for the first time), contains a number of new IP and a No.1 for Nintendo. </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!W8fC!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstac